3) On your “vibranium-like material computer” idea

What you described actually does exist in grounded forms—just not as sci-fi vibranium.

Real analogues:

1. Shape Memory Alloys (SMA)
	•	Deform → apply energy → return to stored shape
	•	“memory” encoded in structure

⸻

2. Ferroelectric materials
	•	Electric field flips internal states
	•	Stores information (like bits)

⸻

3. Memristors
	•	Resistance depends on past current
	•	Literally “remembers” previous states

⸻

4. Piezoelectric materials
	•	Mechanical ↔ electrical conversion
	•	Useful for sensing + actuation loops

⸻

